/technical-overview/.title: Technical overview
/technical-overview/.content:
this section ’ll explains all essential concepts will need know understand what mongock how works

mongock structure

although requieres 3 components work: changelogs driver runner speak about some other concepts
that key works

changelog

simple words changelogs are your migration classes where implement database changes they represent unit execution

migration

migration really component itself ’s operation taking user’s apply them safely order perform desired changes target system normally database see coming sections there operations main one operations just complementary migration such undo list

change entry

mongock tracks executed changes( changelogs) database can deduce which pending applied execute them change entry representation database

driver

this that represents persistence layer everything needs persisted(distributed lock entries etc) passed by driver
although initially conceived only mongodb grown now provides drivers nosql well sql

runner

this kind orchestrator glue put together makes work responsible environment aspect(framework etc) takes with help smaller components loop them

builder

this tightly coupled runner used build runner applying relevant configuration required driver

/.title: What is Mongock?
/.content:
mongock java based migration tool part your application code allows developers have ownership control over data migrations during deployment process allowing safer distributed systems code changes are shipped together

originally designed mongodb product evolving provide wider suite nosql / sql database compatibility cover other feautures transactional execution use cases that require state management systems

our mission enable deploy manage stateful safe reliable manner looking migrating services manner via code mongock best bet
